#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an4.34"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.34:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.34:0.2"
msgid "4. Cakkavagga "
msgstr "4. Situations "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.34:0.3"
msgid "34. Aggappasādasutta "
msgstr "34. The Best Kinds of Confidence "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.34:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, aggappasādā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four kinds of confidence are the best. "

msgctxt "an4.34:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: dvipadā → dipadā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.34:1.3"
msgid "Yāvatā, bhikkhave, sattā apadā vā dvipadā vā catuppadā vā bahuppadā vā rūpino vā arūpino vā saññino vā asaññino vā nevasaññināsaññino vā, tathāgato tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho. "
msgstr "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, is said to be the best of all sentient beings—be they footless, with two feet, four feet, or many feet; with form or formless; with perception or without perception or with neither perception nor non-perception. "

msgctxt "an4.34:1.4"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, buddhe pasannā, agge te pasannā. "
msgstr "Those who have confidence in the Buddha have confidence in the best. "

msgctxt "an4.34:1.5"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti. "
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.34:2.1"
msgid "Yāvatā, bhikkhave, dhammā saṅkhatā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati. "
msgstr "The noble eightfold path is said to be the best of all conditioned things. "

msgctxt "an4.34:2.2"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, ariye aṭṭhaṅgike magge pasannā, agge te pasannā. "
msgstr "Those who have confidence in the noble eightfold path have confidence in the best. "

msgctxt "an4.34:2.3"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti. "
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an4.34:3.1"
msgid "Yāvatā, bhikkhave, dhammā saṅkhatā vā asaṅkhatā vā, virāgo tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ madanimmadano pipāsavinayo ālayasamugghāto vaṭṭupacchedo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ. "
msgstr "Fading away is said to be the best of all things whether conditioned or unconditioned. That is, the quelling of vanity, the removing of thirst, the abolishing of clinging, the breaking of the round, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment. "

msgctxt "an4.34:3.2"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, virāge dhamme pasannā, agge te pasannā. "
msgstr "Those who have confidence in the teaching of fading away have confidence in the best. "

msgctxt "an4.34:3.3"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti. "
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.35, sc4
msgctxt "an4.34:4.1"
msgid "Yāvatā, bhikkhave, saṅghā vā gaṇā vā, tathāgatasāvakasaṅgho tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni aṭṭha purisapuggalā esa bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an4.34:4.2"
msgid "Ye, bhikkhave, saṅghe pasannā, agge te pasannā. "
msgstr "Those who have confidence in the Saṅgha have confidence in the best. "

msgctxt "an4.34:4.3"
msgid "Agge kho pana pasannānaṃ aggo vipāko hoti. "
msgstr "Having confidence in the best, the result is the best. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.34:4.4"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro aggappasādāti. "
msgstr "These are the four best kinds of confidence. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an4.34:5.1"
msgid "Aggato ve pasannānaṃ, "
msgstr "For those who, knowing the best teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:5.2"
msgid "aggaṃ dhammaṃ vijānataṃ; "
msgstr "base their confidence on the best—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:5.3"
msgid "Agge buddhe pasannānaṃ, "
msgstr "confident in the best Awakened One, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:5.4"
msgid "dakkhiṇeyye anuttare. "
msgstr "supremely worthy of a religious donation; "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "an4.34:6.1"
msgid "Agge dhamme pasannānaṃ, "
msgstr "confident in the best teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:6.2"
msgid "virāgūpasame sukhe; "
msgstr "the bliss of fading and stilling; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:6.3"
msgid "Agge saṅghe pasannānaṃ, "
msgstr "confident in the best Saṅgha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:6.4"
msgid "puññakkhette anuttare. "
msgstr "the supreme field of merit—"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an4.34:7.1"
msgid "Aggasmiṃ dānaṃ dadataṃ, "
msgstr "giving gifts to the best, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:7.2"
msgid "aggaṃ puññaṃ pavaḍḍhati; "
msgstr "the best of merit grows: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:7.3"
msgid "Aggaṃ āyu ca vaṇṇo ca, "
msgstr "the best lifespan, beauty, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:7.4"
msgid "yaso kitti sukhaṃ balaṃ. "
msgstr "fame, reputation, happiness, and strength. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "an4.34:8.1"
msgid "Aggassa dātā medhāvī, "
msgstr "An intelligent person gives to the best, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:8.2"
msgid "aggadhammasamāhito; "
msgstr "settled on the best teaching. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:8.3"
msgid "Devabhūto manusso vā, "
msgstr "When they become a god or human, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an4.34:8.4"
msgid "aggappatto pamodatī”ti. "
msgstr "they rejoice at reaching the best.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.34:8.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
